cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach for learning diversified representations in both supervised and self-supervised learning settings. The experiments are conducted on image classification and image reconstruction tasks, indicating that the proposed method is applicable to computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, such as sentiment analysis and text classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses a competitive environment to learn representations, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
